      <hedline>
        <hl1>Flash Trend: Custom Tossing</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Florence Fabricant</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Fabricant, Florence</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Delis and other food shops are suddenly offering custom-made salads assembled by designated tosser from ingredients of customer's choosing, or from set menu; drawing (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Delis and other food shops are suddenly offering custom-made salads assembled by a designated tosser from ingredients of the customer's choosing, or from a set menu. Perhaps they got the idea from Tossed, a salad spot with locations on Park Avenue South and at Rockefeller Center. Could the salad bar the size of a football field, with lunchtime crowds picking over the goods, be on its way out?</p>
